Iranian students are willing to die for their country’s nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear facilities in Iran.
With their gesture they want to express their support for their country’s nuclear program in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students began praying Tuesday at noon outside the facilities and then chanted death slogans to the US and Israel.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around the nuclear technology center in the Iranian city of Isfahan on Tuesday.
They want to show that they are willing to defend their country’s nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, found that Iran, by all indications, is struggling to obtain nuclear weapons.
There is talk in Israel of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students began to pray at noon in front of the Isfahan nuclear facilities and then launched death slogans against the U.S. and Israel.
In the event of an attack, the objective of which would be to paralyze the Iranian nuclear program, according to Israeli sources, not only the Isfahan plant but also the Natanz facility, where uranium is enriched, would be reached.
Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have problems with overweight, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It again demonstrates the importance of the environment where you grow for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessed children feed, for example, on sausages at least twice as often as children from families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence."
In families of overweight children there is no practice of sports, which is applicable to most families today, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was carried out at the end of the last school year and almost 900 elementary school children from all over the Czech Republic participated in it.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children from the 4th to the 8th grade have participated in the project.
A proper diet and plenty of exercise in the family are determinants, which significantly decrease the number of overweight and even obese children.
"Only half of the children surveyed responded that they have five meals per day according to the regimen: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the survey results said.
No breakfast but with sausage for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each breakfasts alone.
But the worst thing was discovering that in 10% of households nothing is eaten at breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, insane chips are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet sodas on a daily basis (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed play sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Build your diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
“The food preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal.”
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
“The popularity of sweet sodas is especially alarming,” the study’s final report warns.
As the main meal, the pasta is taken from the palm and the poultry meat is closely followed.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases a major change in favor of the principles of healthy eating," the results of the study point out.
It draws attention, for example, to sweet sodas, where many children would begin to prefer normal running water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for the main meal and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
