I scream inside, for me it is much better than, for example, Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has recently gained a hundred kilos (please take into account the exaggeration), or the very young Selena Gomez.
The dresses we have to cut them from the magazines or search them on the internet and print them, then elaborate them graphically.
The moodboard, which is what the complete result is called, also expresses our personal style and our relationship with graphic design.
It is also important to think about the graphic part of styling.
The stylist, therefore, does not only wear physically, but also deals, for example, with the pages of products in magazines (concrete topics, such as trends, bags, coats, etc.).
About all this the stylist and designer Mario Kamen<0xC3><0xAD>k told us.
But all this remains for Sunday.
The stylist must have a global vision.
The three specialist guests animated the conference on Saturday with information on all types of bodies.
Stylist Honza Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Ren<0xC4><0x8D>.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to take advantage of this.
And a good stylist knows how to work with the same garment in different ways.
Variability is, in this case, fundamental.
Thus, such a coat (or as they say in English, trench coat) can be dressed to the classic with jeans and t-shirt, but it also serves to dress the naked body with heels and photograph it as if it were actually a dress.
Or you just have to roll it up and up your neck to get a totally different image.
“Play with it,” he insisted.
What I value the most is the following advice: "To start working, you must first know all the rules."
“Then you can break them,” Jakub said.
At last it is clear to me why we memorize all these formulas, what is combined with what, why, if it turns out that in fashion magazines we find different results.
Not to mention the parades.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know that a stylist has to have more types of clothing in reserve than he intends to photograph.
So, for a fashion story that has ten pages (therefore, ten outfits), you have to have prepared, ready to use, at least fifteen.
And besides that the photos the clothes works in combination with other clothes, all of them different from those used in reality.
All this must be taken into account when designing the outfit.
Honza Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD> assured us that image and style alone, in many cases, make up half of the success.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly an extraordinary singer, but the image and the marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, at the moment, there is not yet a clear tendency to use the services of stylists.
Even famous characters find it useless (my skills are enough, my physical appearance is not so important).
And when someone asks us for our services, it should be borne in mind that it is very likely that they will indicate a size very different from their real (minor).
Then you just have to gossip and find out if the magazines of the heart have already written on the subject, if a certain celebrity has become fattened / thinned, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario insisted that it is not enough for the stylist to orient himself in fashion, but he has to understand outfit.
During your work, you should especially communicate with the people you saw, so it is essential to be a good psychologist.
He knows how to value people, he doesn’t miss them, he defends their opinions.
“When a director hires you to classify her wardrobe and complete it with pretty clothes, you can’t take everything and throw it away and say, ‘Oh, how horrible!’”
“Find at least a couple of things that you can ponder and recommend so someone can put them on,” Mario says.
He himself also showed us that everything should fit into the so-called "placovka", that is, the labor market.
This is fixed around the waist and you have there all the necessary tools.
They are objects such as scissors, such as scissors, hair removers, or unmissable. There are also nylon thread (which serves the stylist during the photo session of products such as bags or hats), special clips of hooking clothes ahead, if it was older (pins and other types of hooks are not allowed, as they could damage the fabric), or a sewing set.
In order not to stay in passive listening and put something into practice, we have learned to cover the sole of the shoes.
Even during photo shoots in the studio, on a flat surface, the sole and much more the exterior could be damaged.
And we did nothing but clothe and clothe.
We could not touch the shoes with scissors so as not to damage them by accident.
So you had to be very skillful.
Mario has given me a joy to praise my work unreservedly.
The truth is, I don’t get those skills very well.
This is just a small part of everything we’ve heard throughout the weekend, in the second part of the course.
I’ve already realized that professional styling isn’t a rosy path, but it doesn’t matter what people say.
In Need for Speed: The Run you can compete all over America.
Resen<0xC3><0xA7>a
A journey, in principle carefree, is complicated due to a series of improper neglects of a routine journey during tomorrow's shift.
To a certain extent it was possible to meet expectations, but this does not help, if, in reality, it was not intended to do anything extraordinary.
The new installment, to which The Run is added to the title, aroused high expectations already before its premiere.
It promised to give fresh air to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as shown, appears as a game that should not end up being an action genre again without more.
We are also curious to know how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character gets out of the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case with NFS series, the results don’t vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be taken for granted, but in the total count points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality they cannot even be called errors, but rather they are the incomprehensible failure of the programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphic is equivalent to that of previous installments of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of opponents (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the middle of all this sometimes appears the police, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (specifically there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action is quite suitable for this driving style, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, collisions are no longer the same.
From games of this type you can't expect it to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game restores you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race there are only five resets available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, even resetting doesn’t help, it just helps to learn the given stage from memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civilian" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes sooner or later.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the “surprise” will always happen before your noses.
The adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always advance you in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can spoil the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you will surely be disappointed right away.
And it’s a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the ranking in the race so it doesn’t fit boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is changing cars during races.
You have to be attentive to the gas pumps next to the road, because precisely there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will suffice what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, strong American cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example on curved mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread, there is also a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending up with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is done.
With the car you reach the subway tunnel (pass), where you start to run in the dark on the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km / h (pass) and suddenly, behind you the subway convoy arrives and is carried in front of you without more.
In the drafting we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors really think of us as a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
Well, what a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to be liked by most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for its music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game isn’t over.
The fun is assured, but get ready because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport spotlights.
